tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues displayed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Additional membranous staining was observed in glandular cells of the gastrointestinal tract, gall bladder and fallopian tube. The non-germinal center cells in lymph node displayed strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity. Cells of the central nervous system and male genitalia were negative.

subcellularLocation.summary: Mainly localized to the nucleus. In addition localized to the cytoplasm or vesicles.

tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues displayed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Additional membranous staining was observed in glandular cells of the gastrointestinal tract, gall bladder and fallopian tube. The non-germinal center cells in lymph node displayed strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity. Cells of the central nervous system and male genitalia were negative.
A majority of malignant tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining. Malignant lymphomas, ovarian and colorectal cancers displayed moderate to strong immunoreactivity.
